article.headline: Navy 66, Elon 62
article.story: ELON, N.C. -- Adam Teague scored four of his 11 points during an 8-0 run in the game's final 1:33 to help Navy to a 66-62 comeback win against Elon on Monday night. After Devan Carter's layup put Elon ahead 62-58 with just under two minutes to play, Teague nailed a 3-pointer to start Navy's run, hit a free throw with 14 seconds left to cap it and grabbed a rebound off Carter's 3-point miss to seal the win. Chris Harris led the Midshipmen (11-4) with 14 points, while Clif Colbert and Kaleo Kina scored 13 apiece. Ola Atoyebi and Chris Long scored 14 points each to lead the Phoenix (4-6) and Brett James added 11. Navy hit 13 of 18 free throws in the game, while Elon was 13-for-22 from the line.
